  <skos:Concept rdf:about="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-for/2020/310511">
    <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">Neurogenetics</skos:prefLabel>
    <skos:notation>310511</skos:notation>
    <skos:inScheme rdf:resource="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-for/2020"/>
    <skos:broader>
      <skos:Concept rdf:about="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-for/2020/3105">
        <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">Genetics</skos:prefLabel>
        <skos:notation>3105</skos:notation>
        <skos:inScheme rdf:resource="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-for/2020"/>
        <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-for/2020/31"/>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">This group covers genetics and heredity.</skos:definition>
        <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">a) Microbial genetics is included in Group 3107 Microbiology.
b) Animal genetics associated with animal reproduction is included in Group 3003 Animal production.
c) Genetics of agricultural crops (excl. genetic engineering) is included in Groups 3004 Crop and pasture production and 3008 Horticultural production.
d) Genetic engineering of agricultural crops is included in Group 3001 Agricultural biotechnology.
e) Genetics associated with human health and medicine is included in Groups 3202 Clinical sciences and 3211 Oncology and carcinogenesis.
f) Phylogenetic networks, ontologies and statistical and quantitative genetics are included in Group 3102 Bioinformatics and computational biology.
g) Phylogeny is included in Group 3104 Evolutionary biology.</skos:scopeNote>
