        <skos:broader rdf:resource="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/anzsrc-for/2020/32"/>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">This group covers the processes and function of the human body or the physical and chemical processes involved in the functioning of the human body and its component parts.</skos:definition>
        <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">a) Medical physics and biophysics unrelated to humans are included in Group 5199 Other physical sciences.
b) Basic animal physiology and comparative physiology are included in Group 3109 Zoology.
c) Physiology related to specific aspects of plant or animal production or veterinary practice is included in the appropriate groups in Division 30 Agricultural, veterinary and food sciences.
d) Exercise physiology is included in Group 4207 Sports science and exercise.
e) Nutritional physiology is included in Group 3210 Nutrition and dietetics.
f) Physiological psychology is included in Division 52 Psychology.</skos:scopeNote>
